{"TopicId":156443,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Only one instance of KSP runnning at the same time","CreatedByName":"Carraux","CreatedById":60890,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-14T15:43:37Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Carraux","CreatedById":60890,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-14T15:43:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTitle says it all: Please prevent, that a second/third instance of the game can run parallel to the first. This is very easy to implement, needs less than 5 lines of code.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sal_vager","CreatedById":16426,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-14T16:09:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSome of us run two copies at the same time though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Greenfire32","CreatedById":36705,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-14T16:18:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI feel like this is one of those problems that can be solved by just not running multiple instances at once...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocket In My Pocket","CreatedById":154640,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-14T17:09:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s an Autohotkey script that claims to do just that for any Windows program.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.freewaregenius.com/singleinstance-allow-only-one-running-instance-of-a-program/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.freewaregenius.com/singleinstance-allow-only-one-running-instance-of-a-program/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027ll need Autohotkey obviously: (It\u0027s free.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://autohotkey.com/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://autohotkey.com/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-02-14T17:09:55Z\u0022 title=\u002202/14/2017 05:09  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 14, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Rocket In My Pocket\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"razark","CreatedById":32993,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-14T18:07:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222955044\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487089093\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002236705\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Greenfire32\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Greenfire32 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI feel like this is one of those problems that can be solved by just not running multiple instances at once...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut what about those of us who don\u0027t want to put up with such a convoluted work-around and need a less technical way to handle it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"natsirt721","CreatedById":117557,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-15T06:56:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy is this an issue?? I think Greenfire said it all...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"John FX","CreatedById":59415,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-15T09:45:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou just make another folder with KSP in it, open both folders, run both executables.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI used to have one game on the left monitor, one on the right. One would be mechjeb launching a test flight, the other my main game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"eddiew","CreatedById":127483,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-15T09:49:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s like asking a car manufacturer to remove the ash tray because you personally don\u0027t need it...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"John FX","CreatedById":59415,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-15T11:48:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWait, prevent?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat concept is so far from what my brain regards as a sensible request that it completely failed to understand initially and I thought you were asking how to do it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Carraux","CreatedById":60890,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-15T14:00:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222955044\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487089093\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002236705\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Greenfire32\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 hours ago, Greenfire32 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI feel like this is one of those problems that can be solved by just not running multiple instances at once...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis may happen by accident.\u003Cbr\u003E\n(and two instances running from the same game folder interfere with each other, this doesn\u0027t work).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nC\u0027mon, even \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E can do this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DoctorDavinci","CreatedById":150019,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-16T05:48:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222956132\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487167201\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002260890\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Carraux\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 hours ago, Carraux said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis may happen by accident.\u003Cbr\u003E\n(and two instances running from the same game folder interfere with each other, this doesn\u0027t work).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nC\u0027mon, even \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E can do this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMost accidents are caused by not paying attention\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_rolleyes.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-02-16T05:49:50Z\u0022 title=\u002202/16/2017 05:49  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 16, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by DoctorDavinci\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Phineas Freak","CreatedById":146521,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-16T06:35:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is an easy way via a command line switch:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nCreate a shortcut to the KSP binary.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nOpen the shortcut properties and append the switch \u0022-single-instance\u0022 at the end of the path.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n?\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nProfit!\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ser","CreatedById":104207,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-16T07:14:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222957003\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221487226954\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146521\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Phineas Freak\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n37 minutes ago, Phineas Freak said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is an easy way via a command line switch:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nCreate a shortcut to the KSP binary.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nOpen the shortcut properties and append the switch \u0022-single-instance\u0022 at the end of the path.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n?\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nProfit!\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s the world of software development. Whatever we want to implement is probably implemented already \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}